on, wake up Sam,

49:02.933 --> 49:04.233
Come on wake up, wake up!

49:05.233 --> 49:07.700
One, two, three!

49:08.933 --> 49:10.433
Come on, come on wake up!

49:10.433 --> 49:12.133
One, two, three!

49:14.733 --> 49:15.633
Come on you can't come this far

49:15.633 --> 49:17.200
Just to stop Sam, come on!

49:17.200 --> 49:19.067
One, two, three!

49:19.867 --> 49:21.067
Come on!

49:21.800 --> 49:23.367
One, two, three!

49:25.367 --> 49:26.733
One, two!

49:26.733 --> 49:31.233
(Sad music)

50:02.100 --> 50:03.667
What the hell is the point?

50:06.800 --> 50:10.700
Just come and get me assholes.

50:13.367 --> 50:14.767
Come and get me.

50:21.633 --> 50:23.700
[Voiceover] Brian, Brian?

50:24.433 --> 50:27.267
Oh come on, this is
the best you got guys?

50:28.200 --> 50:29.600
Screw you.

50:29.600 --> 50:32.767
[Voiceover] Brian it's
me, where the hell are you?

50:33.767 --> 50:35.467
Bullshit it's you.

50:35.467 --> 50:36.933
[Voiceover] Oh
you're here too?

50:36.933 --> 50:40.433
Yup on Maria Island
like you told me.

50:41.200 --> 50:42.633
[Voiceover] No, I
told you to stay away

50:42.633 --> 50:43.867
From Maria Island.

50:43.867 --> 50:45.600
There's something
there, a doorway.

50:46.100 --> 50:47.167
A doorway?

50:48.433 --> 50:49.467
And where are you?

50:49.467 --> 50:51.033
[Voiceover] On the other side.

50:51.033 --> 50:52.367
I went through.

50:53.867 --> 50:55.600
That's funny because

50:56.467 --> 50:57.967
I'm looking at your
dead body right now.

50:57.967 --> 50:59.233
[Voiceover] What?

51:00.467 --> 51:02.433
I just found it lying
here next to the river.

51:02.433 --> 51:03.667
[Voiceover] Oh shit.

51:03.667 --> 51:04.833
Yeah.

51:05.500 --> 51:06.933
[Voiceover] I
don't understand.

51:06.933 --> 51:08.733
I'm still alive, I
followed this track

51:08.733 --> 51:10.767
All up the river,
and found a cave.

51:10.767 --> 51:12.233
But there's something
in that cave, Brian.

51:12.233 --> 51:15.067
It's some kind of electrical
doorway to another place.

51:15.067 --> 51:16.800
I think it's where
they came from.

51:16.800 --> 51:18.300
Like an old house.

51:18.300 --> 51:19.800
That's where I am now.

51:19.800 --> 51:21.933
Then why the hell
did you go through it?

51:21.933 --> 51:23.533
[Voiceover] I
thought I saw our dad.

51:23.533 --> 51:25.233
I wanted to apologize.

51:25.233 --> 51:26.600
Apologize?

51:27.600 --> 51:28.933
Mom is dead.

51:29.567 --> 51:31.100
Dad is dead.

51:33.167 --> 51:34.167
And now you're dead.

51:34.167 --> 51:35.233
[Voiceover] Do
you still really

51:35.233 --> 51:36.667
Only think in black and white

51:36.667 --> 51:38.067
After seeing what we've seen?

51:38.667 --> 51:40.667
Tell science to get
lost for just a second,

51:40.667 --> 51:42.267
Believe me Brian.

51:42.800 --> 51:44.800
I have no idea what I've seen.

51:45.900 --> 51:47.067
I don't even know what
the hell I'm talking to

51:47.067 --> 51:48.600
Right now, okay?

51:49.567 --> 51:53.367
All I know is that, Sam is dead.

51:54.933 --> 51:57.467
I have no idea what the
hell I'm gonna do now.

51:58.267 --> 51:59.533
[Voiceover] Keep going.

52:00.367 --> 52:01.833
What?

52:01.833 --> 52:04.533
[Voiceover] If you're going
through hell, keep going.

52:05.900 --> 52:07.300
Are you really there?

52:07.300 --> 52:08.767
[Voiceover] Yes, but
something is holding me here.

52:08.767 --> 52:11.167
I think it's Dad, or (mumbling).

52:11.167 --> 52:12.900
I need your help, Brian.

52:12.900 --> 52:14.800
How am I supposed to
help you if you're dead.

52:14.800 --> 52:16.100
[Voiceover] Go
through the doorway,

52:16.100 --> 52:17.533
Find our old house.

52:17.533 --> 52:19.133
What the hell are
you talking about?

52:19.133 --> 52:20.867
[Voiceover] You'll
wake up in a pool,

52:20.867 --> 52:22.533
Go to the woods and
follow the signs for home,

52:22.533 --> 52:23.933
Through the abandoned buildings.

52:23.933 --> 52:25.100
Please Brian.

52:25.700 --> 52:26.800
Sam?

52:27.133 --> 52:27.900
Sam?!

52:28.433 --> 52:29.233
Sam...

52:31.633 --> 52:36.067
(Foreboding music)

52:43.200 --> 52:44.700
So you're alive huh?

52:53.400 --> 52:54.633
You know?

52:56.667 --> 52:59.533
I used to see ghosts
when I was a kid too.

53:01.600 --> 53:03.200
Back before you were even born.

53:04.900 --> 53:05.933
I never responded
to 'em or anything,

53:05.933 --> 53:08.667
I just didn't want 'em to,

53:08.667 --> 53:10.500
Actually I didn't wanna
get near 'em you know?

53:12.467 --> 53:14.100
I thought maybe I
could trick 'em or,

53:15.067 --> 53:16.233
Play stupid.

53:18.133 --> 53:19.633
I didn't even think I actually

53:20.567 --> 53:22.133
Ever knew what they were.

53:22.133 --> 53:23.500
Until right now.

53:25.100 --> 53:27.133
I mean the last time I
saw them I was probably

53:27.133 --> 53:28.700
I don't know, four or five.

53:31.900 --> 53:35.700
But what I saw was

53:37.200 --> 53:39.400
You looking exactly
like you do right now.

53:41.100 --> 53:42.967
And all you'd ever
say to me was,

53:44.333 --> 53:45.633
"Save me."

53:46.767 --> 53:48.233
Over and over.

53:51.633 --> 53:55.100
I don't know if you
really are Sam or not,

53:57.267 --> 53:59.100
And I don't know if
this is a trap or not,

54:02.300 --> 54:03.833
But I'm coming for you.

54:06.800 --> 54:08.100
All of you!

54:10.500 --> 54:13.200
And I'm gonna send
every last one of you

54:14.300 --> 54:16.067
Back to where you belong.

54:39.767 --> 54:41.800
This message is
for Molly Everett,

54:41.800 --> 54:43.733
Her address is 4085,

54:43.733 --> 54:46.267
Chariot Lane, Santa
Barbara, California.

54:47.967 --> 54:51.067
Molly if you are watching this,

54:52.100 --> 54:54.600
It means I've failed and
that both Sam and I are dead.

54:57.067 --> 54:58.167
I know that

54:58.867 --> 55:00.833
You had a really
hard time growing up,

55:01.700 --> 55:03.367
And I know I was
never there for you

55:03.367 --> 55:04.533
When I should've been,

55:05.267 --> 55:07.200
And I know that
you've been mad at me

55:07.200 --> 55:09.700
For, (mumbling),
coming down here

55:09.700 --> 55:11.600
To try to save my brother, but,

55:12.500 --> 55:14.067
In a classic Dad move,

55:14.967 --> 55:16.133
The problem with the will was

55:16.133 --> 55:19.167
That he didn't even
leave us anything.

55:20.500 --> 55:22.467
He gave everything to some guy.

55:23.100 --> 55:25.133
Some friend of his,
and I've been down here

55:25.133 --> 55:26.267
For a month.

55:26.767 --> 55:28.700
Trying to convince this guy

55:28.700 --> 55:29.867
To give me some money

55:29.867 --> 55:31.867
So I can afford
to see my brother.

55:36.433 --> 55:38.867
But it's okay...

55:40.100 --> 55:41.533
If you do get this Molly,

55:42.200 --> 55:44.733
Please just don't be afraid.

55:45.933 --> 55:49.533
Okay, fear, it's the
easiest emotion to have,

55:50.367 --> 55:51.567
You know that's why
Dad always used it,

55:51.567 --> 55:53.467
That's why he was
always addicted to it.

55:54.467 --> 55:55.667
He would always use it on us,

55:55.667 --> 55:57.333
Whenever his life
wasn't going his way.

55:58.233 --> 55:59.267
And...

56:01.700 --> 56:04.067
Just nothing when we were kids,

56:04.067 --> 56:04.967
When you grew up, nothing

56:04.967 --> 56:06.967
Has ever been your fault, Molly.

56:06.967 --> 56:09.233
Okay, okay?

56:09.767 --> 56:11.967
Don't let Dad's
weakness ruin you,

56:11.967 --> 56:14.933
Don't, just don't let his
bullshit ruin your life.

56:15.700 --> 56:17.400
Okay, because you're
better than that.

56:19.167 --> 56:21.767
Mom and Dad were not our family.

56:22.667 --> 56:25.700
We were our family,
just you, Sam and I.

56:25.700 --> 56:26.933
That's it.

56:27.867 --> 56:29.333
And it always will be.

56:30.667 --> 56:33.333
Just let your bullshit
go and go live your life.

56:34.133 --> 56:35.733
Because you were
always the smartest

56:35.733 --> 56:37.833
Of us, and you were
always the best of us.

56:38.933 --> 56:40.500
And I should've
told you more, but,

56:40.500 --> 56:42.267
I just never did.

56:44.800 --> 56:46.733
Please just go do
something great, Molly.

56:47.733 --> 56:49.367
Because I know you can.

56:51.833 --> 56:53.567
And if you're looking
for Dad's ashes,

56:54.200 --> 56:55.633
I've dig 'em up, in an effort

56:55.633 --> 56:56.833
To finally try to use him

56:56.833 --> 56:58.300
For something good for once.

57:00.767 --> 57:04.733
I wanna use him to help
me save our brother.

57:07.867 --> 57:09.200
Goodbye Molly.

57:09.200 --> 57:13.567
(Sad music)

57:54.133 --> 57:56.467
[Voiceover] This
outbreak cannot be stopped.

57:56.467 --> 57:58.833
I must warn anyone
who hears this.

57:58.833 --> 58:01.367
Stay away from Maria Island.

58:01.367 --> 58:03.067
Something is here.

58:03.067 --> 58:05.433
We have accidentally
opened something.

58:05.433 --> 58:08.133
Some kind of portal
into another world.

58:08.133 --> 58:09.700
We're outside.

58:09.700 --> 58:12.367
We're there now, and
there is no escape.

58:12.367 --> 58:14.267
Do not try and rescue us.

58:14.267 --> 58:16.933
Okay, do not try and rescue us.

58:17.500 --> 58:19.767
This (mumbling).

58:20.333 --> 58:23.333
If you stay here in
Tasmania, you will die.

58:23.333 --> 58:25.500
We are here (mumbling).

58:26.233 --> 58:30.067
Help yourselves to evacuate
from Tasmania at all costs.

58:30.433 --> 58:35.433
(Anticipating music)

59:01.733 --> 59:06.733
(Faint country music)

01:00:23.267 --> 01:00:24.533
[Voiceover] Save me.

01:00:24.533 --> 01:00:25.767
[Brian] Sam!

01:00:26.367 --> 01:00:27.267
Sam?

01:00:27.267 --> 01:00:31.967
(Foreboding music)

01:00:48.133 --> 01:00:49.333
[Voiceover] Brian?

01:00:49.333 --> 01:00:50.600
Brian.

01:00:52.333 --> 01:00:53.800
Keep going, sweet.

01:00:54.933 --> 01:00:56.300
Follow my voice.

01:01:00.133 --> 01:01:01.467
Follow my voice.

01:01:04.333 --> 01:01:05.967
Keep going, sweet.

01:01:09.100 --> 01:01:10.733
You need to hurry Brian.

01:01:13.233 --> 01:01:15.067
Your brother is in trouble.

01:01:23.833 --> 01:01:25.067
Hey Mom.

01:01:25.700 --> 01:01:27.300
[Voiceover] Yes honey.

01:01:27.300 --> 01:01:30.800
I don't have much time
before he takes me again.

01:01:31.633 --> 01:01:32.833
Who Mom?

01:01:33.900 --> 01:01:35.133
[Voiceover] Listen to me.

01:01:35.633 --> 01:01:37.800
Your device will
not work as it is.

01:01:38.567 --> 01:01:40.367
It's not powerful enough yet

01:01:40.367 --> 01:01:41.633
To destroy him.

01:01:41.633 --> 01:01:43.067
What are you talking about?

01:01:43.767 --> 01:01:45.533
[Voiceover] It
needs more energy.

01:01:46.067 --> 01:01:48.700
You must use my soul
as the catalyst.

01:01:48.700 --> 01:01:49.833
What do you mean?

01:01:50.833 --> 01:01:52.467
[Voiceover] Take my necklace.

01:01:54.733 --> 01:01:56.900
Now you have all that I am.

01:01:57.367 --> 01:01:59.867
Place that in your machine
when you activate it.

01:02:00.567 --> 01:02:02.867
Use me as your power source.

01:02:03.533 --> 01:02:04.800
I don't understand.

01:02:05.300 --> 01:02:07.500
[Voiceover] Brian I
am his counterbalance.

01:02:08.600 --> 01:02:10.333
You have to do this.

01:02:10.333 --> 01:02:12.233
It has to be you.

01:02:12.733 --> 01:02:14.767
Or we'll never be free.

01:02:15.400 --> 01:02:16.767
What if I do this?

01:02:16.767 --> 01:02:18.267
What happens to you?

01:02:19.067 --> 01:02:20.567
Will you be gone forever?

01:02:21.067 --> 01:02:22.900
[Voiceover]
Nothing's gone, Brian.

01:02:23.900 --> 01:02:27.100
It's just not there anymore.

01:02:27.667 --> 01:02:28.800
Honey?

01:02:28.800 --> 01:02:30.767
Baby, I'm so sorry
for everything

01:02:30.767 --> 01:02:32.633
You kids had to go through.

01:02:33.767 --> 01:02:36.533
You must do this so that
I can finally help you,

01:02:37.067 --> 01:02:38.567
It's the only way.

01:02:39.333 --> 01:02:40.967
I'm so proud of you Brian.

01:02:42.633 --> 01:02:44.067
I love you Brian.

01:02:45.467 --> 01:02:47.333
I love all of you.

01:02:53.133 --> 01:02:58.133
(Phone ringing)

01:03:04.267 --> 01:03:05.467
[Voiceover] Save me.

01:03:22.133 --> 01:03:23.567
[Voiceover] Hey
Dad, it's Brian.

01:03:24.400 --> 01:03:25.767
Look I know it's been
a really long time

01:03:25.767 --> 01:03:27.300
Since we talked, and,

01:03:27.300 --> 01:03:28.967
I know the last time
didn't go so well,

01:03:28.967 --> 01:03:31.667
But, I just,

01:03:31.667 --> 01:03:33.200
Look Dad, I can't
keep pretending

01:03:33.200 --> 01:03:35.067
Like at you did to
us never happened.

01:03:35.833 --> 01:03:39.233
I've been trying for years, but,

01:03:39.233 --> 01:03:41.300
It just won't go away.

01:03:42.467 --> 01:03:44.100
Every time I see Molly and Sam

01:03:44.100 --> 01:03:45.600
I can see them
where you left 'em,

01:03:45.600 --> 01:03:48.267
And I can see

01:03:48.267 --> 01:03:49.533
How they can't
even look at people

01:03:49.533 --> 01:03:51.167
In the eyes anymore
because of you.

01:03:52.067 --> 01:03:53.167
And it kills me.

01:03:53.900 --> 01:03:55.333
Because unlike you,

01:03:56.100 --> 01:03:57.733
I actually care for
them more than anything

01:03:57.733 --> 01:03:59.100
Else in the world.

01:03:59.867 --> 01:04:02.400
And now since you
are what you are,

01:04:03.300 --> 01:04:05.467
The job to protect
them has fallen on me.

01:04:06.367 --> 01:04:08.200
And I'm sure you'll just
call me overdramatic

01:04:08.200 --> 01:04:09.867
Or a liar like usual, you know,

01:04:09.867 --> 01:04:11.267
Whenever I try to
bring up the truth

01:04:11.267 --> 01:04:12.833
About things you are
probably too drunk

01:04:12.833 --> 01:04:14.067
To even remember.

01:04:15.067 --> 01:04:16.900
But that doesn't mean
it didn't happen.

01:04:17.467 --> 01:04:19.767
You have done some
horrible things to us.

01:04:19.767 --> 01:04:21.867
And ever since I
remember, you've taught

01:04:21.867 --> 01:04:24.167
Me through your actions
that you were the one

01:04:24.167 --> 01:04:27.167
Thing I should fear more
than anything or anyone else.

01:04:27.967 --> 01:04:29.467
But I'm not a kid anymore,

01:04:29.467 --> 01:04:30.667
And I don't have
to bite my tongue

01:04:30.667 --> 01:04:31.667
And pretend like we deserved

01:04:31.667 --> 01:04:33.067
What you did to us.

01:04:33.900 --> 01:04:36.700
I may be your child, but,
I'm not your property.

01:04:37.733 --> 01:04:39.967
Now if you ever want to have
a relationship with me again,

01:04:39.967 --> 01:04:42.100
You need to call me and
finally apologize for what you

01:04:42.100 --> 01:04:43.367
Did to all of us.

01:04:44.833 --> 01:04:45.967
Otherwise,

01:04:46.700 --> 01:04:47.767
This is it.

01:04:49.533 --> 01:04:50.767
Goodbye Dad.

01:04:57.933 --> 01:04:59.600
[Voiceover] Good
evening everybody,

01:04:59.600 --> 01:05:01.100
Tonight we're going to explore

01:05:01.100 --> 01:05:03.867
The dark history of
the Everett family.

01:05:03.867 --> 01:05:05.600
All of their ghosts and demons

01:05:05.600 --> 01:05:08.567
Under the floorboard
will be revealed!

01:05:12.900 --> 01:05:17.100
(Cheerful music)

01:05:30.333 --> 01:05:31.800
Here was the dreaded kitchen

01:05:31.800 --> 01:05:33.267
Where Mommy and Daddy Everett's

01:05:33.267 --> 01:05:35.133
Drinking problem began.

01:05:35.133 --> 01:05:37.433
Daddy would stay up
all night drinking away

01:05:37.433 --> 01:05:40.700
Both his problems
and Mommy's money.

01:05:40.700 --> 01:05:42.300
The children could
be heard yelling

01:05:42.300 --> 01:05:44.667
Into the wee hours
of the morning.

01:05:44.667 --> 01:05:46.633
Poor little Molly, Sam and Brian

01:05:46.633 --> 01:05:48.567
Were defenseless,
and could only watch

01:05:48.567 --> 01:05:50.367
In terror as their parents would

01:05:50.367 --> 01:05:53.467
Turn themselves into monsters.

01:05:58.667 --> 01:06:01.433
The living room, the
television was the children's

01:06:01.433 --> 01:06:04.567
Only friend in this
house of terror.

01:06:04.567 --> 01:06:06.533
A place of sanctuary for them

01:06:06.533 --> 01:06:08.567
To manage their
wounds and pretend

01:06:08.567 --> 01:06:10.833
They had different lives.

01:06:26.567 --> 01:06:28.733
And poor, poor, Sam.

01:06:28.733 --> 01:06:30.533
When he'd see things
his father couldn't

01:06:30.533 --> 01:06:33.233
Understand, he would
become a punching bag.

01:06:33.233 --> 01:06:35.533
This is the dreaded
room where'd he pray

01:06:35.533 --> 01:06:38.967
Every night, not for
the safety of others,

01:06:38.967 --> 01:06:41.900
But the demise of
his own father,

01:06:41.900 --> 01:06:43.400
Praying that one day he wouldn't

01:06:43.400 --> 01:06:45.067
Have to wear long-sleeved shirts

01:06:45.067 --> 01:06:46.467
For the rest of his life

01:06:46.467 --> 01:06:48.167
To hide his secrets.

01:06:48.167 --> 01:06:52.067
Where or where was
his big brother?

01:07:00.567 --> 01:07:02.600
Little Molly's bedroom,

01:07:02.600 --> 01:07:04.300
She thought the
more toys she had,

01:07:04.300 --> 01:07:06.233
The more friends she'd have!

01:07:06.233 --> 01:07:07.800
Unfortunately all they ever did

01:07:07.800 --> 01:07:09.800
Was trap her in the
(mumbling) prison,

01:07:09.800 --> 01:07:13.633
And constantly remind
her there was no way out.

01:07:13.633 --> 01:07:15.467
She became deaf to advice,

01:07:15.467 --> 01:07:17.600
Trapped in her own world.

01:07:17.600 --> 01:07:19.667
No way Brian would
ever come home

01:07:19.667 --> 01:07:23.833
To save them, he'd
never be her hero again.

01:07:36.567 --> 01:07:40.367
And last but not least,
the oldest child, Brian.

01:07:40.367 --> 01:07:43.567
He was always so
quiet, they said.

01:07:43.567 --> 01:07:45.600
He handled their
troubled childhood

01:07:45.600 --> 01:07:47.733
The best, they said.

01:07:47.733 --> 01:07:49.733
Brian was the strong one.

01:07:49.733 --> 01:07:51.467
The devil's advocate.

01:07:51.467 --> 01:07:54.100
Nothing ever got to Brian.

01:07:54.100 --> 01:07:58.300
No one would ever expect
Brian to kill his own parents.

01:07:58.300 --> 01:08:00.167
I didn't kill them.

01:08:00.733 --> 01:08:02.933
[Voiceover] Dad
is dead, Brian.

01:08:02.933 --> 01:08:05.833
(Audience booing)

01:08:05.833 --> 01:08:08.067
It was an accident,
nobody was gonna miss them.

01:08:08.067 --> 01:08:10.833
[Voiceover] Except
poor little Brian.

01:08:10.833 --> 01:08:11.967
What are the odds people

01:08:11.967 --> 01:08:14.333
That some cookie
eggheads opened the door

